      "text": "Okay, here is a brief description:  It can be very hard to make changes in large complicated code bases.  When we make changes its important to know that we are making them one at a time.  Too often we think we are changing only one thing but instead we end up changing other things unintentionally: we end up introducing bugs.  If we can write tests against old code we can figure out when it's behavior is changing.  This helps us know that we've added new code properly and it also supports us when we refactor.  Unfortunately, it's often hard to get tests in place in complicated code.  You have to refactor to get tests in place in order to refactor.  The book shows you now to safely get tests in place to support your work and start to make the code better.  ",
